abstract: If Shirley Hufstedler were a bird, the Audubon Society might tell you to stop looking for her. She can't be observed, at least nut close up. She is either on a dais, in a limousine, behind closed doors or flying too far overhead in an airplane to be accurately sighted.

abstract: The stage darkens. The band strikes up a fanfare. The man steps forward with his head kept low. He is wearing a blazer and a polka-dot bow tie.
